    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhile following the documentation for [autocommands](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lua-guide.html#lua-guide-autocommand-create) the below snippet in config\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TextYankPost', {\n  callback = function() vim.hl.on_yank() end,\n  desc = \"Briefly highlight yanked text\"\n})\n```\n\ngave the below error at the bottom\n```\n4 lines yanked\nError detected while processing TextYankPost Autocommands for \"*\":\nError executing lua callback: /Users/me/.config/nvim-config/init.lua:6: attempt to index field 'hl' (a nil value)\n```\n\nThe error does not occur when we use `vim.highlight`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create `minimal.lua`\n```\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  -- ADD PLUGINS _NECESSARY_ TO REPRODUCE THE ISSUE, e.g:\n  -- 'https://github.com/author1/plugin1',\n  -- 'https://github.com/author2/plugin2',\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TextYankPost', {\n  callback = function() vim.hl.on_yank() end,\n  desc = \"Briefly highlight yanked text\"\n})\n```\n\n2. In the same directory run \n```\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n```\n\n3. In nvim run the below command to edit the `minimal.lua` file\n```\n:e minimal.lua\n```\n\n4. Yank any number of lines\n5. Error pops at bottom\n```\n17 lines yanked into \"+\nError detected while processing TextYankPost Autocommands for \"*\":\nError executing lua callback: /Users/manuraj/code/personal/test/nvim/minimal.lua:14: attempt to index field 'hl' (a nil value)\nstack traceback:\n        /Users/manu/test/nvim/minimal.lua:14: in function </Users/manuraj/code/personal/test/nvim/minimal.lua:14>\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nHighlight should occur without error.\n\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, not sure if this is applicable here\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.4\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
