            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I don't know if this is related, but I was getting the error, when trying to use the context menu inspector in Neovim 0.10.3:\n`Error executing Lua callback: .../neovim/0.10.3/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_inspector.lua:18\n9: attempt to index field 'hl' (a nil value)\nstack traceback:\n        .../neovim/0.10.3/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_inspector.lua:189: in function 'show_p\nos'\n        vim/_defaults.lua: in function <vim/_defaults.lua:0>`\n\nIn the `_inspector.lua` after I changed \n\n```\n-- treesitter\n  if #items.treesitter > 0 then\n    append('Treesitter', 'Title')\n    nl()\n    for _, capture in ipairs(items.treesitter) do\n      item(\n        capture,\n        string.format(\n          'priority: %d   language: %s',\n          capture.metadata.priority or vim.hl.priorities.treesitter,\n          capture.lang\n        )\n      )\n    end\n    nl()\n  end\n```\n\nto \n\n```\n-- treesitter\n  if #items.treesitter > 0 then\n    append('Treesitter', 'Title')\n    nl()\n    for _, capture in ipairs(items.treesitter) do\n      item(\n        capture,\n        string.format(\n          'priority: %d   language: %s',\n          capture.metadata.priority or vim.highlight.priorities.treesitter,\n          capture.lang\n        )\n      )\n    end\n    nl()\n  end\n```\n\nthe error went away.\n`vim.hl` -> `vim.highlight`",
